				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$T-\frac {1}{2}\frac {3}{f_{P}}$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M64"><mml:mi>T</mml:mi><mml:mo>−</mml:mo><mml:mfrac><mml:mrow><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:mfrac><mml:mfrac class="tfrac"><mml:mrow><mml:mn>3</mml:mn></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>f</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>P</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:mrow></mml:mfrac></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12021_2020_9487_Article_IEq15.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> are excluded from further analysis.</p>
        <p id="Par29">Beginning with the first maximum, the section of length Δ<italic>t</italic><sub><italic>A</italic></sub> centered at this maximum is extracted from <inline-formula id="IEq16"><alternatives><tex-math id="M65">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$s_{f_{P}}(t)$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M66"><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>s</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>f</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>P</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:mrow></mml:msub><mml:mo>(</mml:mo><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mo>)</mml:mo></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12021_2020_9487_Article_IEq16.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>. Subsequent sections are centered at such consecutive maxima so that the sections do not overlap (Fig. <xref rid="Fig1" ref-type="fig">1</xref>b). Afterward, those sections are averaged, yielding the averaged low-frequency oscillation <inline-formula id="IEq17"><alternatives><tex-math id="M67">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
