				\begin{document}$s_{f_{P}}(t)$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M84"><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>s</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>f</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>P</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:mrow></mml:msub><mml:mo>(</mml:mo><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mo>)</mml:mo></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12021_2020_9487_Article_IEq24.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> is carried out in the same way but with the length of segments Δ<italic>t</italic><sub><italic>B</italic></sub>. This results in averaged low-frequency oscillation <inline-formula id="IEq25"><alternatives><tex-math id="M85">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
