t the averaged signal does not contain a sinusoidal low-frequency component as extracted through filtration, and the time-frequency maps display a wide range of coupled frequencies. The average spectrum does not contain any prominent peaks, whereas the spectrum of the averaged signal displays characteristic harmonic structure with a maximum not congruent with the maximum in comodulogram. All of those indicators of epiphenomenal origins are much more pronounced for the signal with higher Gaussian spikes amplitude. Visual inspection of auxiliary plots allows us to integrate all of that additional information and confirm the automatically assigned <italic>Ambiguous</italic> origins of the coupling.
